<h2 class="the-real-centre"><strong>Life-shaping books</strong></h2>
<table class="the-real-centre" id="move">
<tr>
<th><strong>Book Title</strong></th>
<th><strong>Book image</strong></th>
<th><strong>What's the book about?</strong> </th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td> You are what you eat </td>
<td><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1328766964i/7845103._UY630_SR1200,630_.jpg" alt="You are what you eat book" width="200"></td>
<td> It was a book I read as a kid, and I remembering being terrified by this, but it also made me open to a lot of foods that other people wouldn't eat.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>The catcher in the rye</td>
<td><img src="https://www.booktopia.com.au/covers/big/9780140237504/0000/the-catcher-in-the-rye.jpg" alt="catching in the rye cover" width="200"></td>
<td> I think it represented that letting go, relaxing and self care is important, even though you have many fears or problems that need to be solved.It made me a lot more comfortable with taking breaks and doing things at my own pace, and not rushing all the time.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>A song only I can hear</td>
<td><img src="https://s3-ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/assets.allenandunwin.com/images/original/9781760630836.jpg" alt="A song only I can hear cover" width="200"></td>
<td>It was a really meaningful book, and it made me be a lot more confident and conscious about my actions. It made me wonder what could happen if you took a leap of faith, and that's why I try to step outside my comfort zone as much as I can. Now I can finally say I'm a devoted Barry Jonsberg reader (not that I couldn't say it before), but I've read almost all his books, except one. Thisbook was also one of the first books I had asked the librarian to order for the school (confidence)!</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>The professor and the housekeeper</td>
<td><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1344313042l/3181564.jpg" alt="The professor and the housekeeper cover" width="200"></td>
<td>It was the most recent and inspiring book I have read, and it made me think outside the box in many situations. The overall storyline and depth of characters was amazing, I would recommend it to everyone.</td>
</tr>
</table>



